        "comment": "As a consequence of new snow and a moderate to strong wind from northeasterly directions, further wind slabs will form from late morning. The old wind slabs of Thursday will be covered with new snow and therefore difficult to recognise. <br/> <br/> The fresh wind slabs can in some places be released, even by a single winter sport participant. In particular on steep slopes the avalanches can be released in the various wind slab layers and reach quite a large size. <br/> <br/> Backcountry touring calls for restraint.",
