      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Over a wide area wind slabs are lying on a hard crust, especially on sunny slopes in all altitude zones, and adjacent to ridgelines and in pass areas at elevated altitudes. <br/> <br/> High altitudes shady slopes: Towards its base, the snowpack is faceted. <br/> Individual weak layers exist in the centre of the snowpack especially on west, north and northeast facing slopes. <br/> <br/> On sunnier slopes where temperatures are less cold, the hard surface of the snowpack will gradually soften over the course of the day. <br/> <br/> In particular adjacent to ridgelines at high altitude snow depths vary greatly, depending on the infuence of the wind."
      },
